io.github.pulsebeat02.minecraftmedialibrary.frame

Class JaffreeVideoPlayer

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.pulsebeat02.minecraftmedialibrary.frame.JaffreeVideoPlayer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    VideoPlayerContext
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LinuxBlockHighlightPlayer, LinuxChatPlayer, LinuxEntityPlayer, LinuxMapPlayer, LinuxScoreboardPlayer

    public abstract class JaffreeVideoPlayer
extends java.lang.Object
implements VideoPlayerContext
    The main abstract class for VideoPlayer classes to extend. Frame Callbacks and Video Players MUST have the correct classes associated with each other! An example of the classes that are linked together can be found below:

    ChatCallback - LinuxChatPlayer

    EntityCloudCallback - LinuxEntityPlayer

    GifIntegratedPlayer - [In Development]

    BlockHighlightCallback - LinuxBlockHighlightPlayer

    MapDataCallback - LinuxMapPlayer

    ParallelVideoPlayer - [In Development]

    ScoreboardCallback - LinuxScoreboardPlayer

    The JavaCVVideoPlayer uses JavaCV (a Java implementation of OpenCV) mainly used for Linux or any other odd ball operating systems that don't have VLC supported. If you are on a Windows or MacOS operating system, it is strongly recommended to use the VLCVideoPlayer players instead as they are much faster and coded in C/C++ libraries.
